The Bush administration on Tuesday is to take the first step toward removing Yellowstone's grizzly bears, a living icon of the American West, from the nation's endangered species list.
Peru's Foreign Ministry said in a terse statement that it was withdrawing its ambassador from Japan in an apparent protest of that country's response to Peruvian attempts to extradite former President Alberto Fujimori.
As the Bush administration prepares to remove Yellowstone's grizzly bears from the endangered species list, a schism has emerged in the environmental movement over whether the bears remain at risk.
